          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-17 14:53:11" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to increase in the extent of or in the instances of an activity or state</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to increase</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to grow</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to spread</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to extend</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>If one assumes that {L:ἐπίγνωσις&lt;SDBG:ἐπίγνωσις:000000&gt;} in {S:05100101000028} is to be understood in the sense of ‘knowledge about’ (see {D:28.18}), then one may translate this expression as ‘you will know more and more about God,’ but if {L:ἐπίγνωσις&lt;SDBG:ἐπίγνωσις:000000&gt;} is to be understood in the sense of ‘to experience knowledge’ (see {D:28.2}), one may ‘you will know God more and more’ or ‘you will come to know more and more what God does.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
